title: New research raises questions about coronavirus immunity: 8% of recovered patients in one study didn't develop antibodies at all
description: Ray Chavez/MediaNews Group/The Mercury News/Getty Images A new study of recovered coronavirus patients found that patients develop different levels of antibodies to the virus. Ten patients of the 130 studied — 8% — didn't have any detectable coronavirus antib…
content:
A new study from Chinese scientists on 130 recovered COVID-19 patients is raising questions about the extent to which people develop immunity to the virus.
